# Cloudflare Pages response headers.
#
# The problem this fixes: without explicit caching rules, an HTML page (e.g.
# chart.html) could be served stale from the browser/edge cache — so a freshly
# deployed page that references a new ?v= asset is never fetched, and chart
# updates appear "not to ship". HTML + scan data are therefore always
# revalidated, while the versioned JS/CSS (busted by the ?v= query on every
# change) may be cached hard. More-specific paths below win on Cloudflare Pages.

# Everything: revalidate by default so the latest deploy is always served.
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff

# Versioned static assets — safe to cache (the ?v= query changes on every edit).
/js/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
/css/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

# Scan output JSON is rewritten every scan — must always be fresh.
/data/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
